1
00:01:49,780 --> 00:01:54,979
[A Dream Within A Dream]

2
00:01:55,009 --> 00:01:58,030
[Episode 26]

3
00:01:59,350 --> 00:01:59,950
Careful, careful.

4
00:01:59,950 --> 00:02:00,680
Slowly, Honey.

5
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:01,280
Careful, careful.

6
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,950
Why did you drink so much?

7
00:02:02,950 --> 00:02:04,560
-Here, be careful.
-I didn't drink much.

8
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:05,150
Easy now, easy.

9
00:02:05,150 --> 00:02:05,640
Hurry!

10
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,990
Let's have two more drinks.

11
00:02:06,990 --> 00:02:07,870
Slow down, slow down.

12
00:02:07,870 --> 00:02:09,070
Take it easy, Father.

13
00:02:10,310 --> 00:02:12,030
Look at you, at your age,

14
00:02:12,030 --> 00:02:13,630
still acting so recklessly.

15
00:02:14,770 --> 00:02:16,280
Keep an eye on him here.

16
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:18,010
I'll go get some hangover soup.

17
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,370
Don't worry, Madam.

18
00:02:21,710 --> 00:02:23,079
Father, seriously,

19
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:26,600
if you can't handle alcohol,
don't push yourself.

20
00:02:26,770 --> 00:02:28,630
Why did you have to drink so much?

21
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:30,720
Look at the state you're in.

22
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,079
Here,

23
00:02:35,430 --> 00:02:36,360
tuck in.

24
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:45,100
Yimeng.

25
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,030
Father,

26
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,190
I'm here.

27
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:51,240
You've always been

28
00:02:51,910 --> 00:02:53,910
the one who can't handle hardship.

29
00:02:55,190 --> 00:02:57,850
Being out there isn't like
being in the capital.

30
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:00,840
You won't have such a big
house to live in,

31
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:02,970
with so many people to take care of you.

32
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:06,910
You should reconsider.

33
00:03:09,030 --> 00:03:09,840
Father,

34
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,360
so you already know?

35
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,910
I sometimes

36
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,840
just play dumb.

37
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:23,820
Not only do I know you're leaving,

38
00:03:25,150 --> 00:03:26,310
but I also know

39
00:03:27,190 --> 00:03:29,710
you're leaving because of Nan Heng.

40
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,190
Right?

41
00:03:41,820 --> 00:03:43,800
I don't know exactly what happened

42
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,430
between you and Nan Heng.

43
00:03:46,590 --> 00:03:48,030
But I believe

44
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:50,920
if there's a misunderstanding,

45
00:03:51,190 --> 00:03:53,000
you should clear it up.

46
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:58,310
But what if the problem

47
00:03:59,150 --> 00:04:00,560
isn't with him,

48
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:03,750
but within my own heart?

49
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:07,310
When he was a good person,

50
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:09,640
I trusted him unconditionally.

51
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:11,840
When he was a bad person,

52
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:14,800
I confronted him without mercy.

53
00:04:16,070 --> 00:04:17,750
When the good and bad person

54
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:19,430
were the same person,

55
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:24,430
I started to hate myself

56
00:04:24,950 --> 00:04:27,390
for no longer being able to trust him.

57
00:04:30,670 --> 00:04:31,480
Father,

58
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:32,830
tell me.

59
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:36,120
When a relationship becomes like this,

60
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:38,090
can it still be called love?

61
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:41,800
I can't even understand
my own heart anymore.

62
00:04:42,390 --> 00:04:43,950
How can I look to the future?

63
00:04:51,830 --> 00:04:52,840
Very well.

64
00:04:55,510 --> 00:04:57,190
Since you want to go,

65
00:04:58,310 --> 00:05:00,950
I'll have someone escort you to Jiangnan.

66
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:04,230
When you've figured things out,

67
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:06,680
I'll send someone to bring you back.

68
00:05:14,660 --> 00:05:19,600
[Laiyi House]

69
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:26,800
My Lady,

70
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,560
have you really thought this through?

71
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:30,070
You won't even take me or Zhixia with.

72
00:05:30,070 --> 00:05:31,800
Who will take care of you there?

73
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:36,390
You have your own plot to follow.

74
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,560
You shouldn't change because of me.

75
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,950
Alright, Yingqiu.

76
00:05:44,070 --> 00:05:45,600
If you really care about me,

77
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,750
just make sure the carriage is spacious

78
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:49,750
and pack me clothes for all seasons.

79
00:05:50,190 --> 00:05:51,000
Most importantly,

80
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,510
ask the kitchen to prepare
some good food for me,

81
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:54,270
okay?

82
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:56,950
Alright, alright,

83
00:05:56,950 --> 00:05:58,560
that's enough, go now.

84
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,270
Just go.

85
00:05:59,270 --> 00:06:00,000
Hurry up.

86
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,170
Where are you going?

87
00:06:26,630 --> 00:06:27,890
How did you get in here?

88
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:29,390
This is my home.

89
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:31,840
I know it's your home.

90
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:35,080
Where are you going with all these things?

91
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:40,159
I'm going wherever I want.

92
00:06:40,390 --> 00:06:41,920
It's none of your business.

93
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,440
So you're abandoning me?

94
00:06:52,270 --> 00:06:53,980
You're an able-bodied man.

95
00:06:54,270 --> 00:06:55,870
Why should I take care of you?

96
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:58,720
You know that's not what I meant.

97
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:10,360
Song Yimeng,

98
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:11,630
Song... Song Yimeng,

99
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:12,600
Song Yimeng.

100
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,270
Everything that happened before

101
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,310
was all my fault.

102
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:19,750
I'm sorry.

103
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,770
Please give me another chance.

104
00:07:26,830 --> 00:07:28,090
What was your fault?

105
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:29,970
What chance should I give you?

106
00:07:32,870 --> 00:07:33,980
Between us,

107
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:34,750
you and I...

108
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:36,010
Enough, stop talking.

109
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:37,760
I'm telling you,

110
00:07:38,430 --> 00:07:40,070
I won't fall for a liar again,

111
00:07:40,630 --> 00:07:42,290
nor will I be made a fool again.

112
00:07:42,510 --> 00:07:43,510
Meeting you

113
00:07:43,950 --> 00:07:46,120
was like tripping on the road.

114
00:07:46,430 --> 00:07:47,510
I was just unlucky

115
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:48,810
and I accept that.

116
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:49,430
I...

117
00:07:49,430 --> 00:07:51,090
So, esteemed Seventh Prince,

118
00:07:51,310 --> 00:07:52,560
leave immediately

119
00:07:52,750 --> 00:07:54,240
and don't ever come back.

120
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,530
I'm not leaving.

121
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:04,960
No matter what you say today,
I won't leave.

122
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,520
Just give me one more chance.

123
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,120
Just give me one more chance.

124
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:09,800
Nan Heng!

125
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:12,370
Can you please stop pestering me?

126
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:13,160
Just go.

127
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:13,560
I—

128
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:14,560
Get out of my house.

129
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,430
Leave now.

130
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:45,280
What do I have to do
for you to forgive me?

131
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,660
Disappear from my sight completely.

132
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:50,390
Don't let me hear your voice

133
00:08:50,790 --> 00:08:52,050
or see your face again.

134
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,200
What if I refuse?

135
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:03,200
Then I'll make you suffer even more.

136
00:09:03,510 --> 00:09:05,960
Since I could expose
Chancellor Gao's affairs,

137
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,390
I can dig up much more.

138
00:09:11,910 --> 00:09:12,720
You mean

139
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,540
you won't marry me anymore

140
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:18,210
and want to be my enemy instead?

141
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:20,630
Is this your answer?

142
00:09:25,550 --> 00:09:26,720
So no matter what I do,

143
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:27,910
you'll never forgive me?

144
00:09:27,910 --> 00:09:28,720
Yes.

145
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:33,000
I will never forgive you.

146
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,030
Never ever.

147
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:59,390
What else do you want to ask me?

148
00:10:00,510 --> 00:10:01,790
Do I like you?

149
00:10:02,630 --> 00:10:03,440
I don't.

150
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,390
Do I hate you?

151
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:08,600
Of course I do.

152
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:10,960
Would things have been different

153
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:12,760
had I known earlier
that you were

154
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,320
the same person?

155
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,780
I'm sorry, Your Highness.

156
00:10:17,990 --> 00:10:19,840
If I had known all this earlier,

157
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:22,320
I would have despised you even more,

158
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,270
hated you even more,

159
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:24,800
and even killed you sooner.

160
00:10:26,910 --> 00:10:28,000
Do you understand?

161
00:10:41,150 --> 00:10:42,000
I understand.

162
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,790
If you understand,

163
00:10:45,390 --> 00:10:46,360
then get out.

164
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:17,380
♪ Trample past the abyss ♪

165
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:22,680
♪ Pick up the ashes of fallen stars ♪

166
00:11:26,650 --> 00:11:29,880
♪ Listen to your memories ♪

167
00:11:30,970 --> 00:11:36,680
♪ Reincarnations are like shadows ♪

168
00:11:38,430 --> 00:11:43,170
♪ After waking, moving against the flow ♪

169
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:49,170
♪ Even if the kiss lands between
truth and illusion, I’m still willing ♪

170
00:11:48,790 --> 00:11:49,750
Leave now,

171
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:50,870
get out of my house.

172
00:11:50,690 --> 00:11:54,050
♪ Above all sounds,
the moon flows like silver ♪

173
00:11:50,870 --> 00:11:51,750
Go now!

174
00:11:55,490 --> 00:12:00,920
♪ The stars fall from the sky ♪

175
00:12:03,090 --> 00:12:07,000
♪ Follow the light
and fall into this maze ♪

176
00:12:08,190 --> 00:12:13,450
♪ In the depths of passing time,
who's still waiting ♪

177
00:12:14,210 --> 00:12:16,670
♪ A single glance back ♪

178
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:22,980
♪ If the vows are vain,
if the journey is too tumultuous ♪

179
00:12:23,810 --> 00:12:27,480
♪ Love and hate intertwine
but won't forget ♪

180
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:32,780
♪ The light shines,
sighs turn into frost ♪

181
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:29,510
My Lady,

182
00:12:29,550 --> 00:12:30,960
the kitchen has prepared over
a dozen desserts,

183
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:31,840
both sour and sweet ones.

184
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,500
Would you like to choose some?

185
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:38,670
♪ Is there still hope
at the end of the wind and snow? ♪

186
00:12:38,150 --> 00:12:38,960
My Lady,

187
00:12:39,750 --> 00:12:40,840
why are you crying?

188
00:12:39,850 --> 00:12:42,180
♪ Your face ♪

189
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:45,260
♪ Even if the road ahead is veiled ♪

190
00:12:46,770 --> 00:12:48,290
♪ And the rest of our story
fades unfinished ♪

191
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:56,660
♪ I'll still choose to meet you ♪

192
00:12:53,550 --> 00:12:54,360
It's nothing.

193
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:56,620
The wind is too strong.

194
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:57,840
It got in my eyes.

195
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:09,170
[Song Residence]

196
00:13:07,790 --> 00:13:08,600
Your...

197
00:13:08,790 --> 00:13:09,600
Uh,

198
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:10,390
General,

199
00:13:10,630 --> 00:13:11,830
did you see Miss Song?

200
00:13:14,150 --> 00:13:16,150
She said she's leaving the capital.

201
00:13:16,150 --> 00:13:17,210
Where is she going?

202
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:26,480
Keep an eye on the Song Residence.

203
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:27,550
Wherever she goes,

204
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:29,150
ensure her safety.

205
00:13:29,630 --> 00:13:30,510
I understand.

206
00:13:33,910 --> 00:13:34,670
General!

207
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,000
General!

208
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:37,630
General,

209
00:13:37,630 --> 00:13:38,600
there's news from the palace.

210
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:42,600
The Noble Consort is going to plead
with His Majesty for Chancellor Gao.

211
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:53,670
[Fengyi Palace, the late empress' palace]

212
00:13:57,540 --> 00:14:02,620
[Memorial Tablet of Late Empress Yurong]

213
00:14:22,270 --> 00:14:24,630
You shouldn't be here.

214
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:28,380
I have no other choice, Your Majesty.

215
00:14:28,860 --> 00:14:29,910
Liangzhou is harsh and cold,

216
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:31,570
with sand storms everywhere.

217
00:14:31,630 --> 00:14:33,120
My brother is too old

218
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:34,520
to endure such hardship.

219
00:14:35,150 --> 00:14:36,880
I beg for Your Majesty's mercy.

220
00:14:37,390 --> 00:14:39,960
I can give up my title as Noble Consort.

221
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:41,360
I can go guard the imperial tomb.

222
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:43,600
I just want my brother to live.

223
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:44,790
Your Majesty,

224
00:14:45,750 --> 00:14:47,150
I'm begging you.

225
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:03,520
Your Majesty,

226
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:06,300
what must I do

227
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,550
for you to spare my brother?

228
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:16,840
As long as Nan Heng surrenders
the Xuanjia Army's command token,

229
00:15:17,910 --> 00:15:19,960
I can spare Gao Changyin.

230
00:15:20,510 --> 00:15:22,370
But if Heng surrenders the token,

231
00:15:22,390 --> 00:15:23,840
those wolves in the court

232
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:25,240
will surely harm him!

233
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:26,730
Wolves?

234
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:30,340
Do you know

235
00:15:30,870 --> 00:15:34,150
who are the wolves that keep me awake

236
00:15:34,150 --> 00:15:35,390
at night?

237
00:15:38,260 --> 00:15:41,700
They are your precious son
and your dear brother.

238
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:50,770
My brother

239
00:15:51,790 --> 00:15:53,590
has indeed made grave mistakes.

240
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:56,580
But what wrong has Heng done?

241
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:59,790
He personally sent his own uncle
to the imperial prison.

242
00:15:59,790 --> 00:16:00,600
Your Majesty,

243
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:03,200
why do you still
make things difficult for him?

244
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:04,960
Is it

245
00:16:05,550 --> 00:16:08,150
just because he is my son?

246
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:22,520
Fine.

247
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:26,120
So all the blame

248
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:28,120
falls on me.

249
00:16:32,050 --> 00:16:34,390
I know my sins are grave.

250
00:16:36,150 --> 00:16:38,190
Please grant me death.

251
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:41,270
Mother, you don't need to blame yourself.

252
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:42,150
Get out!

253
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:44,920
Your Majesty,

254
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:46,910
I couldn't stop him.

255
00:16:48,890 --> 00:16:49,690
Your Majesty,

256
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:51,240
everything is my fault.

257
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:52,790
It has nothing to do with Mother.

258
00:16:52,790 --> 00:16:53,720
Your Majesty,

259
00:16:53,740 --> 00:16:55,140
please do not punish her.

260
00:16:55,630 --> 00:16:57,650
I told you to get out.

261
00:16:57,910 --> 00:16:59,270
Did you not hear me?

262
00:17:00,270 --> 00:17:02,190
Is this a place you should be in?

263
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,720
It's my fault.

264
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:04,750
I shouldn't have come.

265
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:06,480
Your Majesty, blame me.

266
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:07,920
Don't punish Heng.

267
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,030
Very well!

268
00:17:09,829 --> 00:17:11,310
In the Empress's chambers,

269
00:17:11,310 --> 00:17:12,480
you two

270
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:14,339
still dare to be so presumptuous!

271
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:17,790
I don't dare.

272
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:27,329
I don't dare.

273
00:17:27,349 --> 00:17:29,160
I think you definitely dare.

274
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:32,790
The Empress died because of you.

275
00:17:34,310 --> 00:17:35,640
Do you want her to

276
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:37,790
not find peace, even in death?

277
00:17:38,830 --> 00:17:40,960
If you weren't my son,

278
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:42,240
I would have killed you

279
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:44,030
on that grassland years ago.

280
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:48,310
I thank Your Majesty

281
00:17:49,030 --> 00:17:50,030
for your mercy.

282
00:17:50,270 --> 00:17:51,030
You...

283
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:07,310
Fine.

284
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:08,790
Heng.

285
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:11,090
There are some things

286
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:12,540
I need to make clear

287
00:18:12,790 --> 00:18:14,200
to you today.

